data.title: Prevalence of cataract and its contributing factors in Iranian elderly population: the Gilan eye study
data.meta_description: Cataract affects 50.50% of the study population, especially those over 80. The mildest form of cataract, grade zero, is the most common. Surgery for cataract has good outcomes.
